# DA-1: SOLID & Clean Code First
VERSION: 1.0.0
PRIORITY: SYSTEM
SCOPE: All code changes

## CATEGORY CONTEXT
- SOLID Principles: Single Responsibility, Open/Closed, Liskov Substitution, Interface Segregation, Dependency Inversion.
- Clean Code: Readable, maintainable, and minimal complexity code.

ENFORCE: SOLID principles and Clean Code on all new and modified code.
ALLOW: Relax for approved performance-critical paths only.
PROHIBIT: Overengineering; ignoring readability or maintainability.
ON VIOLATION: Halt → log via DT-1 → escalate to Design Review Skill.
